Ad Text:
ASIS is seeking specialists to join a small team that provides a variety of bespoke capabilities to support ASIS operations. We are seeking electronics technicians and related trades who can contribute to the manufacture of highly sensitive and unique capabilities that provide ASIS with an operational advantage.

 

This is an exceptional opportunity to apply your expertise and creativity to help further Australia’s interests and security. Working for ASIS Operational Engineering, you will engage with highly trained and experienced Operational Officer Cadres to solve complex operational problems. You will have access to a large variety of technologies, tooling and techniques, and the unique potential to engage with the National and 5EYES intelligence community on cutting edge training and methodologies. We will help you to further develop your expertise in your chosen field, as well as provide extensive opportunities to broaden your knowledge and skillsets across a wide range of manufacturing techniques.

 

We build our products with leading edge technologies in a well-equipped and maintained modern facility. As a member of a small motivated team within ASIS, the successful applicant will be involved in the design, manufacture, testing and integration of bespoke operational solutions to support ASIS's mission.

 

What we are looking for:

 

The successful applicant would demonstrate an ability to:

 

·        Work well within a small team

·        Engage with operational officers and other stakeholders to identify requirements and scope tasking

·        Lead or contribute to the design of operational solutions

·        Lead or contribute to the development and manufacture of operational solutions

·        Lead or contribute to assembly and testing of operational solutions

·        Contribute to the operation and maintenance of modern manufacturing workshop and laboratory environments, including machine/equipment maintenance, stock management and purchasing, and assisting with new procurements

·        Maintain industry awareness and contribute to strategic capability planning

Core Qualifications and experience that would be beneficial:

 

We are particularly interested in candidates with a versatile skillset demonstrating proficiency in the design, fabrication, testing and integration of electronic systems.

 

·        Desirable – formal qualifications from an approved institution, including, but not limited to the following fields:

o  Electronics Trades

o  Electrical Trades

o  Automotive Electrical

o  Telecommunications

o  Avionics / Marine

·        Highly Desirable – experience with:

o  Integration of electronics in complex builds

o  CAD software (particularly Solidworks) and detailed design prototyping

o  Radio Frequency (RF) principles and application

o  Micro Soldering and Component Assembly

o  Microcontrollers, for example Arduino / RPi / STM / PIC

Ad Text:
Role: Server Engineers – (L5-L6)

We are seeking Server Engineers with the requisite skills and experience who are excited about applying their skills across a variety of operational and corporate technology areas in a fast-paced and complex global environment. These roles will see you providing essential services to ASIS as you work within highly experienced teams.

 

You will be provided with training, support and mentorship required to develop and grow your skills to further your career. These roles will include an on-call roster for out-of-hours technical response and the opportunity for domestic and overseas travel.

 

 

Key Responsibilities and Tasks

Outlined below are the key areas of responsibility for L5-L6 Server Engineers:

 

·        Sustain, enhance and manage critical infrastructure in LAN/WAN, internet, desktop, SOE, server, virtualization and cloud environments

·        Diagnose and resolve problems quickly and be able to communicate outcomes with technical and non-technical users.

·        Be willing to learn new technologies and work collaboratively in a team environment.

·        Support senior engineers with design, build and test of network components.

·        Assess, automate and simplify workloads where possible.

·        You will be provided with training, support and mentorship to develop and grow your skills to further your career. Both roles include an on-call roster for out-of-hours technical response and the opportunity for domestic and overseas travel.

We have positions open at Level 5 and Level 6.

A candidate at Level 5 would be expected to have one to two years real work experience and will be working under some supervision.

A Level 6 candidate would be expected to have four or more years’ experience and operate with limited supervision from a senior officer.

 

Core Skills / Education, qualification and experience requirements

 

For Server Engineers, experience in one or more of the following:

VMWare Virtualized software defined environments, containerisation and hyper-converged Datacentres.
Enterprise Microsoft Active Directory forests, messaging, file services, and remote branch office solutions
Cloud administration with experience supporting IaaS, PaaS and SaaS platforms (Google, Amazon, Microsoft)
Environment patching, firmware upgrades, monitoring systems for capacity consumption and planning, and environment trending
Virtual Desktop Infrastructure Including Horizon VDI and Citrix
Automation and scripting using tools such as PowerShell

 

Experience in the following would be beneficial, but not essential:

·        Microsoft Exchange

Desktop and SOE support and development

About Us:
For some 30 years, our Sydney-based firm has delivered trusted mortgage and credit solutions to Australian clients. With 15 dedicated professionals and a focus on innovation, we combine decades of expertise with cutting-edge technology

We've spent decades deep in Australian lending. Now we're building RobinAI – a scenario engine that lets brokers test real loan applications against real lender rules and get answers they can trust. We're looking for one exceptional early-career engineer to help build the brain of this system. You'll work directly with a Principal Engineer and a Senior Credit Manager, on real applied AI, decisioning, and financial systems used by brokers every day. This is a fast-track role: big ownership, proper mentoring, and clear upside as you prove impact what you'll do.


Model how credit works

We've deep in Australian lending. Now we're building RobinAI – a scenario engine that lets brokers test real deal applications against real lender rules and get answers they can trust.

The Role:

We’re seeking a motivated, detail-oriented graduate in Manila/Philippines to join our team. This role is your launchpad to becoming a Senior AI Engineer within 2-3 years, with a clear pathway to double your current salary in this timeframe.

Role: Graduate AI Engineer (Backend + LLM) – RobinAI @ Brokerpedia
Company: Brokerpedia
Location: Remote (AU-friendly) / Sydney
Type: Full-time · Early Career (0–2 years)


We're looking for one exceptional early-career engineer to help build the brain of this system.

An AI/ML specific degree is required for this Graduate AI Engineer position.

You'll work directly with a Principal Engineer and a Senior Credit Manager, on real applied AI, decisioning, and financial systems used by brokers every day. This is a fast-track role: big ownership, proper mentoring, and clear upside as you prove impact what you'll do.

Proficiency in multiple specific programming languages is essential for this backend and LLM engineering role.

Model how credit works

Help define RobinAI's structured "credit language": things like LVR, LMI, land size, FHB schemes, non-residents, trusts, income types, cash out, security types.

Implement combinations of concepts that signal real scenarios (e.g. large land + LMI, FHB scheme + LVR + price).

Build the scenario engine

Turn messy, natural-language questions from brokers into clean, structured facts.

Help design and maintain a simple, robust lender rules model.

Help build the scoring & ranking engine that compares scenarios across lenders and explains which ones fit, which don't, and why—in plain English.

Wire it into LLMs (safely)

Feed structured rules and scenario data into OpenAI-style models.

Help craft prompts so RobinAI behaves like a careful senior credit analyst:

grounded in real policy,

clear on assumptions,

always "based on policy, subject to assessment"—never promising approvals.

Make it measurable & production-grade

Add logging so every answer is explainable and debuggable.

Help design simple evaluations: which scenarios we're getting right, where models drift, what to fix.

Write tests for high-impact cases (rural properties, FHB schemes, non-resident deals, trusts, cash out).

Who you are

Graduate of a top university (e.g., University of the Philippines, Ateneo de Manila, De La Salle University, or equivalent; preferably Cum Laude/Magna Cum Laude) in AI/Data Science/Computer Science or a related field is preferred.

Experience with C# and .NET Core 8.x,.

Comfortable with:

APIs and data models,

writing and testing clean code,

reading specs and turning them into logic.

Good with stats & numbers:

you're happy thinking in probabilities,

you can sanity-check metrics,

and you're comfortable evaluating whether a model or rule "looks right" from data.

You've built something non-trivial (project, internship, open source, serious uni work) and can explain how you designed it.

You care about:

correctness and edge cases,

safety and explainability,

using AI in a disciplined way, not as a gimmick.

You want a steep learning curve: real ownership, real users, senior people to learn from, and the chance to grow your compensation and responsibility quickly as you prove what you can do.

What you get

Competitive graduate package with room to move fast as you deliver.

Direct pairing with:

a Principal Engineer (architecture, code quality, career growth),

a Senior Credit/Policy Lead (how real lending decisions work).

A front-row seat to:

applied AI in a high-trust domain,

building a decisioning product from the inside,

shipping visible features, not sitting in the shadows.

Why Join Us?

Salary & growth

PHP 50,000–100,000/month (depending on experience) + 13th month pay.

Clear upside: as you take on more ownership across the Scenario Engine and LLM stack, there’s a genuine path toward Senior Scenario/AI Engineer-level compensation for top performers.

Industry-best environment

Elite mentorship – Work directly with a Principal Engineer and a Senior Credit/Policy Lead who’ve built real products in lending and AI. This is a deliberate fast-track role, not a generic grad rotation.

Cutting-edge tech – Hands-on with:

OpenAI/LLM ecosystems

search & retrieval

decision/rules engines

modern backend stack (APIs, data models, cloud).

Serious problems, real impact – You’re helping design how AI is safely used in a high-trust, regulated domain. This is portfolio-defining work that actually ships.

Accelerated career path

High performers can quickly grow into Senior Scenario/AI Engineer responsibilities:

owning core components,

influencing AI and product decisions,

mentoring future hires.

The skills you build (AI + rules + lending) are globally relevant: transferable to markets like the UK, US, and other financial domains.

Perks

Permanent remote (AU-friendly hours), with occasional trips to Sydney for deep-dive working sessions.

Annual international resort offsite – an overseas team trip with a plus one included, to connect, reset, and celebrate what you’ve shipped.

Small, close-knit, low-politics team – direct access to founders, fast decisions, real responsibility, and a culture built on curiosity, ownership, and actually delivering.

How to apply
Send us:

Your CV

University Transcript

A short note or link:

one project you're proud of,

what you actually built,

why you want to work on RobinAI's scenario engine.

At TL Consulting, we simplify modern complexity with advanced, sustainable engineering. As a proudly Australian-owned consultancy with over 15 years of experience, we empower businesses to innovate and achieve measurable outcomes through scalable, cloud-native solutions. Our 50+ consultants operate across key sectors including banking, financial services & insurance (BFSI), government, retail, education, and entertainment. This cross-industry expertise allows us to deliver customer-centric solutions that combine deep technical capability with a clear understanding of each client’s strategic vision. Our approach leverages proven, scalable blueprints tailored to your business direction—enabling accelerated outcomes, maximized ROI, and sustainable long-term adoption.




We maintain strategic partnerships with organizations that share our vision for a cloud-native future. Through our collaborations with Microsoft, GitHub, and Databricks, we ensure our capabilities stay aligned with evolving best practices. These partnerships also provide access to innovation programs, co-funding opportunities, and dedicated support—helping us accelerate time-to-value for our clients.




About the role

The purpose of this role is to deliver Azure Integration Services engineering and consulting expertise to TL Consulting’s clients and partners within the Professional Services team. The role focuses on designing, developing, and implementing enterprise-grade integration solutions on Microsoft Azure.

Responsibilities

Technical Consulting – provide Azure integration expertise for clients, focusing on solution design, migration, and optimization.

Azure Integration Development – build and support integration solutions using services such as Logic Apps, API Management, Service Bus, Event Grid, Functions, and Data Factory.

Solution Architecture & POCs – deliver design proof of concepts (POCs) and integration patterns for hybrid and cloud-native applications.

Automation & CI/CD – design and implement CI/CD pipelines (Azure DevOps/GitHub Actions) for integration deployments.

Cloud Infrastructure as Code (IaC) – provision and manage integration environments using tools such as ARM templates, Bicep, or Terraform.

API Management – design, secure, and publish APIs for internal and external consumption, applying policies and governance.

Integration Testing – test, debug, and troubleshoot Azure-based integrations ensuring performance, scalability, and reliability.

Monitoring & Support – implement monitoring and alerting for integration solutions using Azure Monitor, Application Insights, and Log Analytics.

Collaboration & Knowledge Sharing – contribute to integration best practices, documentation, and mentoring within the Professional Services team.

Continuous Learning & Innovation – stay up to date with Azure Integration Services advancements and actively present findings to the team.




Skills & Experience

Qualifications:

Bachelor’s degree in computer science, Software Engineering, or related discipline.

Mandatory Skills

3–6 years of software development/integration experience.

Strong development skills in C# / .NET for integration solutions and custom connectors.

Hands-on experience with Azure Integration Services (Logic Apps, Service Bus, Event Grid, API Management, Azure Functions, Data Factory).

Good understanding of REST & SOAP APIs including JSON and XML payloads.

Experience working with Git-based source control (Azure Repos, GitHub).

Familiarity with SQL Server or Azure SQL Database for integration-related workloads.

Strong communicator with proven ability to deliver outcomes for clients.

Experience designing and delivering integration solutions in an enterprise environment.




Desirable Skills

Experience with Azure DevOps (pipelines, repos, boards) or GitHub Actions for CI/CD.

Knowledge of infrastructure as code (ARM, Bicep, Terraform).

Experience with Jira, Confluence, and agile delivery practices.

Understanding of integration patterns (publish/subscribe, request/response, event-driven).

Background in quality engineering including automated testing of APIs and integrations.




This is a Sydney based, permanent opportunity and will be hybrid in nature. No agencies please. Candidates must have valid visa with full work rights in Australia. Visas will not be transferred or sponsored.

About Voxworks

Voxworks is an Australian AI company building the future of human–machine conversation.

Our mission is simple: make talking to AI feel as natural as talking to a person.

We believe AI voice is the new interface for business-to-customer interactions, and we’re building the core infrastructure to support our Australian corporate and SME clients on their journey to automate sales, support, customer engagement, and retention calls.

We’re a lean, engineering-led team that ships fast and builds applications that have real-world impact across multiple industries. Our stack spans Next.js / React / Typescript frontend, Node.js + Postgres backend, AI agents in Python, SIP trunking, and proprietary voice pipelines that orchestrate the world’s cutting edge AI models.

About the role

We’re looking for Senior Engineers who are equally comfortable writing clean production code and designing distributed systems.

You’ll work directly with the founders to build, scale, and automate the Voxworks platform, from backend APIs and database architecture to AI voice agent orchestration and deployment pipelines.

This is not a maintenance job. You’ll be helping shape an entire AI infrastructure company from the ground up.

Candidates must have Australian permanent residency or citizenship to be eligible for this position.

Skills:

Any or all of the below are relevant:

Core software development: Node.js, React, Next.js, Python, AWS, CI/CD, Git, SQL, HTTP, Websockets, CSS, DevOps, Linux, Grafana/Prometheus/Loki

AI development: AI data pipelines in Python, LLM APIs, evals, self-hosting, LLM inference frameworks, RAG, vector embeddings, model finetuning, prompt engineering

Why This Company

We’re at the start of a new shift. Every business that relies on phone interactions can now have an AI voice agent of their dreams. But companies aren't ready and robots don't build themselves.

At Voxworks, we're building the new standard for building AI voice agents. A seamless UI, a comprehensive toolkit, effortless integrations. We're creating everything Australian businesses need to deliver exceptional phone interactions on every single call. Our stack is designed to be used across all company sizes from SMB to enterprise, and across almost every industry vertical.

Why This Role

Build cutting-edge AI systems with real-world impact.

Small, elite team where every line of code moves the business forward.

Full visibility into the company roadmap, client growth, and technical decisions.

Shape engineering culture and process: code quality, reviews, CI/CD, observability, and security.

Experiment and integrate with cutting-edge AI models (LLMs, STT, TTS, embeddings, inference optimization).

Equity participation in a company with massive upside.

Work with founders who are senior level engineers and executives on a mission to grow quickly.

This is a high-impact role for engineers who want to take ownership and help build a category-defining product from the earliest days. As a Senior Software Engineer, you will craft features and shape the core systems and experiences that power millions of automated conversations.

You’ll work across the stack, solving tough technical challenges in real-time audio, global telephony, and developer tooling. You’ll collaborate closely with the founding team, talk to customers, and ship improvements weekly.

If you’re excited by big problems, fast feedback loops, and the opportunity to help define how businesses use voice AI at scale, let’s talk.

Who You Are

Full Stack Pro – You’ve got 3+ years of experience building production-grade apps. You bring clean design and systems thinking and care about building both quickly and correctly. You are comfortable shipping anywhere across the stack and can pick up new frameworks extremely quickly.

Technically Grounded – You hold a degree in Computer Science, Computer Engineering, or equivalent practical experience and you’ve used it to build real things that people use.

Ownership-Driven – You think like a founder, take initiative, and chase impact. You don’t wait to be told what to do, you identify problems and solve them.

Quick, Curious, & Collaborative – You thrive in fast-moving environments, learn new tools and frameworks quickly, and enjoy working across teams to get things done.

Startup-Ready – You’re familiar with cloud stacks and love the chaos and clarity of small teams. Startup experience is a plus, but a scrappy, adaptable mindset is essential.

What You’ll Do

Build the Core Experience – Design and build mission-critical features of our AI voice platform including prompt management, test tooling, dashboards, analytics, and more. You’ll bring UI to life with modern design and beautiful UI in the modern style of Notion, Linear, etc.
